Step 2 — Handle your 720×1280 frame size (critical)
Your frames are 720×1280, but the model requires height and width divisible by 14 (DINOv2 patch size) — 720 and 1280 are not, so passing them directly will crash. The dataset resizes every frame to a configured image_size, so you just pick a 14-divisible target that preserves your 16:9 aspect ratio. I verified these options:
OptionSize (H×W)NotesLight (less VRAM)448 × 798aspect-perfect, good for tight GPUStandard518 × 924matches Depth-Anything-V2 scale; recommendedIf OOM392 × 700smallest sensible
You pass this on the command line as --image-size H W (note: height first). No config edit needed. I recommend starting with 448 × 798 given your GPU constraints.
