Critical reminders
Use the same --image-size in all four commands (steps 4–7). If you train at 448×798 but evaluate at a different size, results will be wrong.
Resuming after a crash: add --resume runs/phaseN/ckpt_XXXXXX.pth (latest checkpoint in that phase) and the trainer picks up from that step.
If you raised max_depth to 30 earlier (for your 30m depth question), make sure it's set in both gid_custom.yaml and instance_depth.yaml, and that your annotations were generated with that value — otherwise keep it at 10.
One thing worth confirming before you commit GPU-days to this: glance at a few runs/phase1.log loss values in the first ~500 steps. If the loss is flat or NaN from the start, stop and check — that usually means a depth-unit or max_depth mismatch between your annotations and the config, which is far cheaper to fix now than after two days of training.
